\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Cybersecurity is a critical field focused on protecting computer systems, networks, and data from unauthorized access, attacks, and damage. As cyber threats become more sophisticated, cybersecurity measures have evolved to include advanced techniques such as artificial intelligence, machine learning, and behavioral analytics. Common cybersecurity practices involve the use of firewalls, encryption, multi-factor authentication, and intrusion detection systems. Industries such as finance, healthcare, and government place a high priority on cybersecurity to safeguard sensitive information and ensure operational integrity. The continuous development of cybersecurity strategies is essential to counteract emerging threats and vulnerabilities.}